metadata.name: No more diplomacy
metadata.description:
February 24, 2022 - Russia starts a war against Ukraine. Thousands of innocent people have died as a result of bombings and illegal military attacks.

The world has responded with harsh sanctions. The UN General Assembly has suspended Russia's membership in the UN Human Rights Council.

18 countries have sent 318 Russian "diplomats".

Hundreds of companies refused to cooperate with the occupying country.
